com.usebottles.bottles (2021.7.14-treviso) precise; urgency=low

  * Dependencies can be extracted and installed from a Windows cabinet
  * Dependencies can override and move dll
  * Dependencies can now install fonts without user intervention
  * Dependency/installer manifests, support environment variables and arguments
  * If versioning is active for the bottle, a new state is created before installing a dependency
  * Dependencies and installers now call their uninstaller, if this is declared in the manifest
  * Now you can search for dependencies using the search field
  * Dependencies and installers show the source license
  * When a crash report appears, reporting it the issue is automatically and correctly filled
  * While creating a new state, information about the entire process is shown on the screen
  * Support for vkd3d
  * The search for installed programs has been extended to user AppData
  * Fixed some problems related to the dxvk implementation
  * Now dxvk and vkd3d are installed only after the user presses Install on first start
  * Reduced the amount of logs
  * Flatpak now uses the app directories
  * If there are bottles in the old dir and the app dir is empty then a migration dialog is shown
  * Fixed a bug in Nvidia identification for optimus laptops
  * Fixed a bug in the management of the download manager that resulted in a crash
  * Install dxvk and vkd3d on bottle creation if missing
  * The preferences are organized into sections
  * The program list is hidden if empty
  * The bottle details page now uses a sidebar
  * Added references to documentation for some features
  * Makes the UI more consistent with rounded edges and status pages from libhandy
  * Replacing the name wine with runner, where possible
  * Added more information for initial download to the Onboard
  * French translations thanks to @julroy67
  * Portuguese (Brazil) translations thanks to @LeandroStanger
  * Hungarian translations thanks to @ovari
  * Chinese (Simplified) translations thanks to Flywater Zh
  * Portuguese translations thanks to @laralem
  * Czech translations thanks to @pervoj and Vojtěch Perník
  * Spanish translations thanks to @fitojb
  * Esperanto translations thanks to @phlostically
  * Croatian translations thanks to @milotype
  * New logo thanks to @jannuary @alvarlagerlof @ZekeSmith


 -- Mirko Brombin <send@mirko.pm>  Wed, 14 Jul 2021 00:00:00 +0000
